The paper deals with the problem of finding interesting associations in data, which is a core problem in data mining and machine learning. The paper proposes a sampling-based method for this problem, which is a common approach in these fields. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses similarity measures and association rules, which are topics that fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper mentions experiments on standard association mining benchmarks, which suggests that it may also be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
